external_knowledge:
Quality control status 'passed' implies that the products have met the required quality standards; 
ISO certification means the products comply with the International Organization for Standardization; 
Certification expiry date indicates when the certification becomes invalid; 
Cumulative inventory and orders refer to the total quantity of products stored and ordered over time, respectively.

- 'Running low' refers to products where the current quantity is less than or equal to the reorder level; 
- Compliance status is determined by a future certification expiry date; 
- Recent orders are those placed within the last 30 days; 
- The latest revision is determined by the highest version number for each product specification.
